        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Nakht</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Parsed info (not mine) shows Shackle of Spirit at 50%, Tepid Deeds at 70%, and Turgur's Insects at 75%.  These are MR based slow spells.  Shaman also get a 25% disease based slow for high MR, but possibly low or moderate PR, mobs.</P><P>A resisted slow will often generate more aggro than a successful slow.</P><P>Anyone with a superior slow not being able to overwrite ours is due to a level/stacking/overwrite issue.</P><P>By the way, wanting to pre-slow in DN prior to the assist call to help the raid is certaintly nice of you, just be careful where you aggro the construct to.  On top of the enchanters and clerics would be bad, for example.</P><P>By the way, your guild's shaman, who have been able to slow since level 5 as well as the beginning of time, have a reason for not "pre-slowing" on named or just plain big mobs as they may do in normal exp groups.</P><P>Might consider asking them why as well as tips on aggro management outside of HS/Veil or FD.</P><P>However good the intention, not clearing something like this with your guild/groupmates (so they what to expect and how to respond) is generally not a good thing.</P><P>Nakht Takharu - 58 Defiler - Conclave of the Damned - 7th Hammer</P><P> </font></td>
